children.description: Meisje in Axelse streekdracht met fiets. Het meisje draagt over de ondermuts en het oorijzer een 'trekmuts'. Ze draagt 'dubbele strikken' (dubbele, klaverbladvormige gouden oorijzerhangers) aan de 'krullen' (oorijzeruiteinden) van het oorijzer. Voorop de fiets is een carbidlantaarn bevestigd.

children.title: [Boy on a bicycle]
children.description:
Title assigned by cataloguer.
Original note by John Thomas '4888. Smithers 2 cab Best'.
Note on library envelope 'Smith A Boy on A Bicycle'.
Duplicate negative 3560.
Computer file. Aberystwyth: National Library of Wales, 2001-2002. (John Thomas digitisation project). Original file captured in uncompressed TIFF format. Cropping, image size, unsharp masking, gamma correction and compression settings for screen res JPEG were made using Adobe Photoshop v6.0.1 and Abobe Imageready v3. Nexscan F4100; Linocolor v6; Custom built acid free card mount to hold glass plates from scanner bed; no validation key, no encryption, no watermark. Made from duplicate negatives. Target resolution of Approx. 1200ppi to allow production of 2094x1694 @300ppi exhibition prints; Screen-res copies use JPG commpression at approx 35%; 8bit; Hi-res TIFFs use grayscale with gamma of 1.8; Apple Colorsync. No control targets.
2001-2002 ; scanned. Reprographic Unit, National Library of Wales, Aberystwyth, Ceredigion.

children.title: A man on a bicycle with a physician riding pillion...
children.description:
Lettering: When father fetched the doctor. Lion's Head brand. Cricks & Martin Ltd., London. Doctor's name-plaque on the house in the background: "Dr Spills surgeon"
A man on a bicycle with a physician riding pillion; advertising the film "When father fetched the doctor". Colour lithograph, 191?. Lettering note: Doctor's name-plaque on the house in the background: "Dr Spills surgeon" The doctor has grabbed his medical bag. His top hat goes flying as the father races off with him to a medical emergency. Date of the film given as 1912 in the Internet movie database but as 1915 in the British Film Institute database (both accessed 11 January 2010).

children.title: Werbeplakat für National-Fahrräder
children.description:
Nationalgefühle und Götterwelt helfen verkaufen. Auf einem Fahrrad gelingt es dem Götterboten Merkur, einen Jockey problemlos abzuhängen. Freihändig, denn die Fahne des Deutschen Kaiserreiches und Siegeslorbeer wollen festgehalten sein.
Mit Luft gefüllte Radkränze, wie hier im Bild, kamen 1888 zuerst in Irland auf, "um die auf die Nerven wirkenden Vibrationen der Maschine dämpfen zu können" (Illustrierte Geschichte der Erfindung des Fahrrades, 1906).
Im Jahre 1897 waren in den Fahrradfabriken Deutschlands ungefähr 55 000 Arbeiter beschäftigt.  (Museum Schloss Moritzburg Zeitz)

children.title: Motocycles and bicycles on Talimhane Square
children.description: Six men with two motorcycles and several bicycles on Talimhane Square. Two men are alongside each motorcycle. A man in a hat bends over the vehicle closer to the camera, another wearing a leather cap and a suit is watching, with his left hand in his trouser pocket. Two men wearing flat caps, one of them of African origin, are crouched next to the motorbike in the rear. Behind them, a man with a bag over his right shoulder and an unidentifiable round object in his left hand is walking away from the scene, pushing a bicycle with his right. A sixth man on the right margin of the photograph is surveying another bicycle. In the foreground, five more bicycles are scattered between the men and the photographer's position, all of them fixed-gear bikes. At Talimhane Square, people used to fix, rent and ride bicycles and motorbikes. From the late 1920s, the square was gradually built up.

children.title: Stativ, för montering av cykel
children.description:
Stativ för montering av velocipederna TM4286-TM4289. Lösa tillbehör: tre rörstänger, 30 st. krampor, fyra förnicklade hylsmuttrar, tre längre bultar med muttrar av olika slag, en liten platta, en hållare, skiftnyckel och två fasta nycklar.
O.P Nelson innhade 1914 ett autogarage med verkstad och bensinstation vid Östra Tullgatan i Malmö och från 1923 var han återförsäljare och hade en fabrik på Excercisgatan 12. Cyklarna TM4286-TM4290 lämnades till Tekniska museet på 25-årsdagen av hans broder John Nelsons bortgång. Han hade dött vid en cykeltävling i Amerika. Cyklarna hade använts av brodern och dennes "pacemakers" vid tävlingar i början av 1890-talet. Tillverkad i Amerika.

children.title: Roberts Jānis Strazdiņš velo izbraucienā ar "Ērenpreisiem"

children.title: How the Germans generate electricity for wireless in the trenches
children.description:
A soldier sitting on a stationary bicycle. The wheels of the bicycle have been removed and it has been adapted to sit on a free-standing frame. According to the original caption, this contraption has been developed to generate electricity. The equipment necessary to convert the pedal power into electrical power is fitted to the rear of the bicycle. This young soldier is providing a demonstration. He is in full uniform and is wearing a steel helmet, and a bag round his neck. Due to appalling conditions in the trenches, and the frequent absence of proper equipment, soldiers became incredibly resourceful in discovering ways of overcoming particular problems. The contraption shown here is an excellent example of the lengths that some men went to. [Original reads: 'OFFICIAL PHOTOGRAPH TAKEN ON THE BRITISH WESTERN FRONT IN FRANCE. How the Germans generate electricity for wireless in the trenches.'].
Electronic reproduction of:; How the Germans generate electricity for wireless in the trenches.; 1 photograph : black and white ; 15.30 x 20.20 cm.

children.title: Cycle orderlies under fire
children.description:
Cyclists sheltering from shelling, Western Front, during World War I. A shell bursting in the rubble of ruined buildings beside a road. Two cyclists have turned their bikes upside down and are using the wheels to give a little shelter from the blast. Curiously, a third man, appearing totally unconcerned, seems to be using a hammer and chisel on a rock in the road. Bicycles were used quite commonly, not only for general transport, but also for carrying dispatches. Motorbikes, runners, pigeons and dogs were also used to carry messages because field telephones were limited by the need for cables and wireless was still unreliable. [Original reads: 'Cycle orderlies under fire.'].
Electronic reproduction of:; Cycle orderlies under fire.; 1 photograph : black and white ; 16.40 x 21.50 cm.

children.title: Werbeplakat der schwedischen Firma HUSQVARNA
children.description:
Werbung auf Sportkleidung hat, wie hier zu sehen, auch eine längere Tradition, nur selten gelingt sie so "ideal" doppelsinnig.
1906 waren übrigens von 450 000 Kopenhagenern 30 000 Fahrradfahrer.  (Museum Schloss Moritzburg Zeitz)

children.title: Cykel
children.description: Trehjulig cykel. Styrning med högerhandshandtag som påverkar kugghjul-kuggstång. Bromshandtag för vänsterhand. Kedjedrift. Två stora bakhjul, ett litet framhjul och "damsadel", vilken är mycket trasig. Massiva däck. Märkning: The Royal Mail Tricycle, på sköld av mässing. Röd dekal: The Royal Machine Manufacturing Co Ltd, Birmingham.
